name: Fisherman and waterfall
description:
This is my artwork of two men fishing with a net by the waterfall.
It may be interesting to know that standing net fishing is a type of fishing in which the net is placed vertically and the bottom hangs under its own weight. This fishing is done both in the river and from a boat in the middle of the sea.
Ancient Egyptian artifacts dating back to 3000 BC can be found in fishing nets.
